1581
01:13:47,549 --> 01:13:52,179
or a probability that
subprime losses stop at 5%?

1582
01:13:52,387 --> 01:13:53,455
Thank you.

1583
01:13:53,555 --> 01:13:58,352
I would say it is a very
strong probability, indeed.

1584
01:13:58,852 --> 01:14:01,396
So back to the residential sector.

1585
01:14:01,522 --> 01:14:03,590
When we rolled out the new
variable rates package...

1586
01:14:03,690 --> 01:14:06,193
- MARK: Excuse me.
- Um... (CHUCKLES)

1587
01:14:07,694 --> 01:14:08,762
Yes, sir.

1588
01:14:08,862 --> 01:14:12,241
Zero! Zero!

1589
01:14:12,366 --> 01:14:15,102
There is a 0% chance

1590
01:14:15,202 --> 01:14:18,981
that your subprime losses will stop at 5%.

1591
01:14:19,081 --> 01:14:20,149
- Zero.
- (CELL PHONE CHIMES)

