in financial regulation, right?

1647
01:16:36,134 --> 01:16:38,220
No. No.

1648
01:16:39,304 --> 01:16:41,848
(GASPS) Hey! Dougie!

1649
01:16:42,683 --> 01:16:45,627
Hey! Come over here.
What are you doing at Caesars?

1650
01:16:45,727 --> 01:16:47,229
He's at Goldman.

1651
01:16:47,854 --> 01:16:48,881
See you.

1652
01:16:48,981 --> 01:16:54,011
We can do BBB-level swaps
at 500 basis points. Maybe.

1653
01:16:54,111 --> 01:16:57,890
You're pricing the swaps
like the bond is gonna collapse

1654
01:16:57,990 --> 01:17:00,367
even though the bond value's
going up? Really?

1655
01:17:00,909 --> 01:17:01,977
Sign of the times.

1656
01:17:02,077 --> 01:17:03,078
CHARLIE: What the hell is going on?

1657
01:18:01,970 --> 01:18:05,749
Lewis, can you come in
early tomorrow, please?

1658
01:18:05,849 --> 01:18:08,126
I need to unload the AIG and Countrywide

1659
01:18:08,226 --> 01:18:09,670
and Freddie Mac positions

1660
01:18:09,770 --> 01:18:12,272
so that we can afford
the premiums on the...

1661
01:18:12,439 --> 01:18:13,423
(SIGHS)

1662
01:18:13,523 --> 01:18:16,443
...core mortgage shorts on the swaps.

1663
01:18:16,902 --> 01:18:18,403
No problem, Dr. Burry.

1664
01:18:20,447 --> 01:18:21,615
- Dr. Burry?
- Hmm?

1665
01:18:23,533 --> 01:18:24,534
(CLEARS THROAT)

1666
01:18:25,202 --> 01:18:29,081
If the investors withdraw,
what's going to happen here? Are we done?

1667
01:18:29,206 --> 01:18:31,124
Honestly, I don't know.

1668
01:18:35,379 --> 01:18:37,089
(STAMMERS)

1669
01:18:38,799 --> 01:18:41,051
The bonds aren't going down.

1670
01:18:42,302 --> 01:18:44,971
They won't move. It's possible

1671
01:18:45,389 --> 01:18:49,976
that we are in a completely
fraudulent system.

1672
01:18:51,395 --> 01:18:54,064
Or... (STAMMERS) You're wrong.

1673
01:18:58,819 --> 01:18:59,903
Sure.

1674
01:19:00,654 --> 01:19:04,658
It's possible I'm wrong.
I just don't know how.

1675
01:19:09,371 --> 01:19:13,542
I guess when someone's wrong,
they never...

1676
01:19:13,917 --> 01:19:16,169
They never know how.

1677
01:19:20,465 --> 01:19:21,508
LEWIS: See you in the morning.

1678
01:19:21,633 --> 01:19:22,676
Yeah.

1679
01:19:24,469 --> 01:19:26,471
Even Bear upped their prices.

1680
01:19:27,055 --> 01:19:29,541
And they keep calling us Brownhole.

1681
01:19:29,641 --> 01:19:31,251
You just don't have the money
or the reputation.

1682
01:19:31,351 --> 01:19:32,686
Don't take it personally.

1683
01:19:32,811 --> 01:19:34,087
I don't think I have
the strip club in me tonight.

1684
01:19:34,187 --> 01:19:37,841
I'm just gonna get some ginger ale
and watch some pay-per-view.

1685
01:19:37,941 --> 01:19:40,318
I'll book us some flights out
for the morning.

1686
01:19:41,736 --> 01:19:44,348
CHARLIE: (STAMMERS) A deal.
We need a deal, right? A deal.

1687
01:19:44,448 --> 01:19:46,241
We need a deal we can afford.

1688
01:19:46,366 --> 01:19:48,643
We need a deal
that they're not gonna refuse.

1689
01:19:48,743 --> 01:19:52,080
So... What can we do? We can...

1690
01:19:53,373 --> 01:19:56,276
The AA tranches. What if we
bet against the AA tranches?

1691
01:19:56,376 --> 01:19:57,711
Who's not gonna take that bet?

1692
01:19:58,420 --> 01:20:01,323
We know they say they're 95% AAA-rated,

1693
01:20:01,423 --> 01:20:03,408
but in reality they're more like 25%.

1694
01:20:03,508 --> 01:20:05,911
Some of them are 0%!

1695
01:20:06,011 --> 01:20:08,622
We also know that if
the bottom tranches fail at over 8%,

1696
01:20:08,722 --> 01:20:09,873
the upper tranches are affected.

1697
01:20:09,973 --> 01:20:11,183
They go to zero.

1698
01:20:11,433 --> 01:20:14,394
I'll bet you right now
that those AA's are actually like B's.

1699
01:20:14,853 --> 01:20:17,939
I rarely ever say these words,
but I think Charlie's right.

1700
01:20:18,273 --> 01:20:19,941
Look, Ben.

1701
01:20:21,610 --> 01:20:23,028
The payoff

1702
01:20:23,528 --> 01:20:24,930
is 200 to 1.

1703
01:20:25,030 --> 01:20:27,073
But they're all taking
the ratings at face value.

1704
01:20:27,199 --> 01:20:30,577
So they're charging pennies
on the dollar a bet against the AA's.

1705
01:20:32,204 --> 01:20:35,023
Just when I start thinking
you guys are clowns...

1706
01:20:35,123 --> 01:20:37,609
No one on the planet's
betting against AA's.

1707
01:20:37,709 --> 01:20:40,612
The banks will think we're either high
or having a stroke.

1708
01:20:40,712 --> 01:20:43,048
They'll take every dime we have to offer.

1709
01:20:45,634 --> 01:20:46,968
Kinda brilliant.

1710
01:20:48,762 --> 01:20:50,831
This is what we did
that no one else thought of.

1711
01:20:50,931 --> 01:20:53,834
Not even Baum or Burry
thought to short the AA's.

1712
01:20:53,934 --> 01:20:55,293
But we did.

1713
01:20:55,393 --> 01:20:56,937
Little Brownhole Capital.

1714
01:20:57,270 --> 01:21:02,175
We're interested in shorting
some of the AA tranche of CDOs.

1715
01:21:02,275 --> 01:21:04,052
Come on, guys, what's the angle?

1716
01:21:04,152 --> 01:21:06,446
Oh, got no angle.
We're new to this. We're just excited.

1717
01:21:06,571 --> 01:21:10,283
We want to do $15 million
in swaps on the AA tranche.

1718
01:21:10,742 --> 01:21:11,810
I don't understand.

1719
01:21:11,910 --> 01:21:14,538
You can buy as much
AA tranche as you want.

1720
01:21:16,748 --> 01:21:18,859
$40 million against the AA.

1721
01:21:18,959 --> 01:21:21,169
Brother, I will sell you
as much as you want.

1722
01:21:21,461 --> 01:21:23,672
You understand perfectly, Bob.
